Description:
Hi guys,

I don't have access to the SA account on VOY-Oliver so escalating for you guys to take a look.

Please action the following and confirm back:

Stop the Oliver "Jboss" service ("SoftlinkOliver").

Change the name of the server.log file

(C:\Program Files (x86)\Softlink International\Library Server\log)

Then login to SQL Server Management Studio and expand the listing under the Oliver Database entry in SQL Server Management Studio, then expand the "Tables" folder and "right-click" on "dbo.l3_Corporation" and select "Edit Top 200 Rows", then enter the word "True" (excluding the quotation marks) in the following fields (to replace the existing entry - which is usually "False") on the top row (ONLY the one that IS NOT "l3_uuid" of "master" or "NULL"):-

l3_Startup, l3_RunScripts, l3_RebuildIndex and l3_LoadReports.

Then exit SQL Server Management Studio and start the Oliver service.

Confirm back to me once done

Thanks,

Jimmy

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Police Cyber Alarm Support <support@cyberalarm.police.uk>
Date: Thu, 23 May 2024 at 17:19
Subject: Police CyberAlarm Data Collector Query
To: hflavell@ahs.pmat.academy <hflavell@ahs.pmat.academy>


Good afternoon,



We have recently issued an email to the reporting contact on your Police
CyberAlarm registration form. The email sent was explaining that you are
not an active member of Police CyberAlarm, as our system has triggered a
flag, concerning your Police CyberAlarm Data Collector.



The original email (included below) received a bounce back from your mail
server. This occurred as the email address associated with your Police
CyberAlarm account was incorrect, these details have since been updated to
this email address. Could you please confirm that this is the correct email
address for correspondence regarding potential vulnerabilities and
notifications from the Police CyberAlarm service. If you would like to
update these details, we are able to assist with this, alternatively, once
your collector is back up and running you will be able to review all the
contact details associated with your Police CyberAlarm Membership.



Please see below for the original email:



*Thank you for completing the registration process and becoming a member.
Our records indicate you have installed and registered your Data Collector,
however your Police CyberAlarm Report has triggered a flag on our system
that currently your collector is not supplying data.*



*Police CyberAlarm works by analysing the data that you send to the
collector, this has allowed the service to help stop live attacks, help
resolve thousands of vulnerabilities and to provide detailed advice for
securing member networks. Unfortunately, if no data reaches the collector,
we are unable to provide the service level we would like to.*



*We are aware that some members have not completed the last step of the
setup or may have had issues with the configuration of the collector or
their firewall logging. To assist with this, our support engineers will be
running several web meetings for organisations over the coming weeks.*



*If you are available and would like one of our team to help with the setup
of your collector, please respond to this email with the contact details
for the person you would like us to work with and we will get this set up
as soon as possible.*



*Yours sincerely,*



*The Police CyberAlarm Team*





Kind Regards,

*The Police CyberAlarm Team*

Hi Mike,

I'm so sorry to backtrack after you've put in the leg work, but having
caught up with Meg and met Calvin/mum, I think he is going to need to go
into the nurture group - or at least be in A band to access the Applied
Learning pathway. Meg may well have spoken to you about this already.

Calvin hasn't been in education for the past 9 months and was struggling
with his education prior to this. He has ADHD for which he will be
expecting to take medication when he returns after half term. Mum has
suggested he is accustomed to having 1:1 support in school previously and
has asked about whether we will honour this here. I have explained if he
does go into nurture there will be at least 2 SAs in there supporting. Meg
spoke to the family preemptively about nurture and mum is really keen for
this, thinks it is what Calvin needs.

Please can this be considered - it would be great if we can finalise things
before he starts on Monday. Apologies for the short notice, I've only had
the chance to meet with mum just now.

Thanks,
Jessa

Good afternoon,



Thanks for your time earlier.



As discussed, Louise was attempting to log in with l.jackson@ebor.academy,
however, the value (unique identifier) that Azure (Entra ID) is passing
back to iTrent is l.jackson@eboracademy.onmicrosoft.com



When you had the SSO scoping call, as per the requirements email, you
specified that you wished to use Email as the Azure unique identifier.



The options to resolve this are:



   1. The correct unique identifier needs to be specified as part of the
   SSO App config in Azure or the Email value in Azure for each employee needs
   to be updated to reflect: l.jackson@ebor.academy
   2. Or the ‘User Email’ field against the User iTrent account (User
   Details) needs to be updated to reflect the value that Azure is sending.

dnscmd /RecordAdd pmat.academy b._dns-sd._udp PTR pc-printer-discovery.pmat.academy

We are delighted to announce that we are offering four of our most popular online courses completely free of charge! That's right - free!

Don't hesitate to register your interest, as spots are filling up quickly. This is an incredible opportunity that you won't want to miss. You can easily sign up on our website at www.wefindanylearner.com/book-online/ or by contacting our team at 01226 958 888.

All you need to do is meet a few simple criteria, including being at least 19 years old by August 31st, 2023, residing in England, and not currently enrolled in an apprenticeship program.

Enrol today and let's make a difference together!

Lean Organisation Management Level 2

A lean organisation provides the greatest customer value with the fewest resources, a philosophy increasingly important in today’s competitive business market. A sound understanding of the concept and benefits of a lean environment, as well as knowledge of business techniques and working in teams, is essential.

Mental Health First Aid Level 2

It’s important that employers are transparent and open about mental health issues, and this qualification builds an understanding of mental health problems and the support available to colleagues. Increasing the understanding of the mental health of staff at all levels builds a culture of care and support.

Introduction to Neuroscience in Early Years Level 2

This qualification’s aim is to provide an introduction to the early development of the brain in babies and young children from birth to 7 years of age. It looks at how the social brain develops, the limbic system, and self-regulation.

[required] Title: Fwd: Windows 10 upgrade coming soon - how to time your two-hour upgrade
Description:
Hello,

Is this anything we need to do?

Many thanks
Sally

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: ICT Service Desk Mailbox <ictservicedesk@york.gov.uk>
Date: Mon, 13 May 2024 at 15:06
Subject: Windows 10 upgrade coming soon - how to time your two-hour upgrade
To: All CYC Staff <AllCYCStaff@york.gov.uk>


Dear colleagues,



*Windows 10 upgrade coming soon*



Over the next month all CYC issued laptops and desktop computers need to be
upgraded to the latest version of Windows 10 (22H2) to ensure our systems
are secure. The upgrade will take approximately two hours so we advise that
you make sure it takes place when you don’t need access to your computer.



*What you need to do*



When your computer is due to be upgraded, you will see a pop-up message
headed *Windows 10 Critical Update* as below:





**Please note: We would recommend that you upgrade your computer at the end
of your working day, ensuring that any laptops are *plugged in and charging*.
Once the upgrade has started *DO NOT SWITCH OFF YOUR LAPTOP/PC*
**

Follow the instructions in the Windows Upgrade Guide
<https://colin.york.gov.uk/besupported/ict/software-and-systems/windows-10-upgrade/>
 which includes screenshots to guide you through the process of setting the
time for your upgrade. If you don’t set a time, your computer will
automatically upgrade after a named time and date.



*Support*



For any queries relating to the upgrade, please email
CYCLaptopUpgrade@york.gov.uk.



For some devices with limited data storage capacity the upgrade may not be
possible remotely. ICT are aware which devices these are and will contact
you to resolve this. Be aware that we may need to arrange for the upgrade
to be done from West Offices.



Thank you for your support



*ICT team*

I'm having problems again with OneDrive/Sharepoint on one of the children's accounts.

She has gone into powerpoint, and saved a number of presentations in her Documents. I asked her to upload one of these to Teams so she can present it to the class, but when she tried to upload from her Documents folder, there are no presentations in there. Twitter: *@rufforthschool*




---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: ICT Service Desk Mailbox <ictservicedesk@york.gov.uk>
Date: Mon, 13 May 2024 at 15:06
Subject: Windows 10 upgrade coming soon - how to time your two-hour upgrade
To: All CYC Staff <AllCYCStaff@york.gov.uk>


Dear colleagues,



*Windows 10 upgrade coming soon*



Over the next month all CYC issued laptops and desktop computers need to be
upgraded to the latest version of Windows 10 (22H2) to ensure our systems
are secure. The upgrade will take approximately two hours so we advise that
you make sure it takes place when you don’t need access to your computer.



*What you need to do*



When your computer is due to be upgraded, you will see a pop-up message
headed *Windows 10 Critical Update* as below:





**Please note: We would recommend that you upgrade your computer at the end
of your working day, ensuring that any laptops are *plugged in and charging*.
Once the upgrade has started *DO NOT SWITCH OFF YOUR LAPTOP/PC*
**

Follow the instructions in the Windows Upgrade Guide
<https://colin.york.gov.uk/besupported/ict/software-and-systems/windows-10-upgrade/>
 which includes screenshots to guide you through the process of setting the
time for your upgrade. If you don’t set a time, your computer will
automatically upgrade after a named time and date.



*Support*



For any queries relating to the upgrade, please email
CYCLaptopUpgrade@york.gov.uk.



For some devices with limited data storage capacity the upgrade may not be
possible remotely. ICT are aware which devices these are and will contact
you to resolve this. Be aware that we may need to arrange for the upgrade
to be done from West Offices.



Thank you for your support



*ICT team*

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: ICT Service Desk Mailbox <ictservicedesk@york.gov.uk>
Date: Mon, 13 May 2024 at 15:06
Subject: Windows 10 upgrade coming soon - how to time your two-hour upgrade
To: All CYC Staff <AllCYCStaff@york.gov.uk>


Dear colleagues,



*Windows 10 upgrade coming soon*



Over the next month all CYC issued laptops and desktop computers need to be
upgraded to the latest version of Windows 10 (22H2) to ensure our systems
are secure. The upgrade will take approximately two hours so we advise that
you make sure it takes place when you don’t need access to your computer.



*What you need to do*



When your computer is due to be upgraded, you will see a pop-up message
headed *Windows 10 Critical Update* as below:





**Please note: We would recommend that you upgrade your computer at the end
of your working day, ensuring that any laptops are *plugged in and charging*.
Once the upgrade has started *DO NOT SWITCH OFF YOUR LAPTOP/PC*
**

Follow the instructions in the Windows Upgrade Guide
<https://colin.york.gov.uk/besupported/ict/software-and-systems/windows-10-upgrade/>
 which includes screenshots to guide you through the process of setting the
time for your upgrade. If you don’t set a time, your computer will
automatically upgrade after a named time and date.



*Support*



For any queries relating to the upgrade, please email
CYCLaptopUpgrade@york.gov.uk.



For some devices with limited data storage capacity the upgrade may not be
possible remotely. ICT are aware which devices these are and will contact
you to resolve this. Be aware that we may need to arrange for the upgrade
to be done from West Offices.



Thank you for your support



*ICT team*

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: ICT Service Desk Mailbox <ictservicedesk@york.gov.uk>
Date: Mon, 13 May 2024 at 15:06
Subject: Windows 10 upgrade coming soon - how to time your two-hour upgrade
To: All CYC Staff <AllCYCStaff@york.gov.uk>


Dear colleagues,



*Windows 10 upgrade coming soon*



Over the next month all CYC issued laptops and desktop computers need to be
upgraded to the latest version of Windows 10 (22H2) to ensure our systems
are secure. The upgrade will take approximately two hours so we advise that
you make sure it takes place when you don’t need access to your computer.



*What you need to do*



When your computer is due to be upgraded, you will see a pop-up message
headed *Windows 10 Critical Update* as below:





**Please note: We would recommend that you upgrade your computer at the end
of your working day, ensuring that any laptops are *plugged in and charging*.
Once the upgrade has started *DO NOT SWITCH OFF YOUR LAPTOP/PC*
**

Follow the instructions in the Windows Upgrade Guide
<https://colin.york.gov.uk/besupported/ict/software-and-systems/windows-10-upgrade/>
 which includes screenshots to guide you through the process of setting the
time for your upgrade. If you don’t set a time, your computer will
automatically upgrade after a named time and date.



*Support*



For any queries relating to the upgrade, please email
CYCLaptopUpgrade@york.gov.uk.



For some devices with limited data storage capacity the upgrade may not be
possible remotely. ICT are aware which devices these are and will contact
you to resolve this. Be aware that we may need to arrange for the upgrade
to be done from West Offices.



Thank you for your support



*ICT team*

Consolidated Workstation Patch 2 fault code.

Dear Colleague,

ESS have advised that there is an issue with consolidated workstation patch 2, which is triggering a fault code Cannot find Table 11 or 12  in SIMS when you are trying to generate the school census.

An amended patch (Consolidated Workstation Patch 2 - School Census Early Years & DAF) has been supplied by ESS and this has been released to your school via SOLUS.

The next step to take is to request that your IT team run the updated patch by following the process below:

Where School ICT would normally carry out your upgrade we are scheduling this upgraded patch to be deployed.  The fileset will then need to be reimported once this has been applied.

  1.  Open SOLUS3 Deployment UI on the server - Usually located as a desktop icon.
  2.  Navigate to Settings | SOLUS3 | Updates and run a 'Get Updates' button, making sure that 'from the last 3 months' has been selected in the drop-down menu.  You should see a box appear; please make sure that consolidated workstation patch 2 is included

[cid:b3ec7c4b-c36e-4700-80b1-cf2f00989ec6]

  1.  Restart the SOLUS3 deployment service within services.msc.
  2.  Download and re-deploy the patch.
  3.  Apply fileset 2701 again
  4.  Fileset 2701 is suitable for uploading the return however the DfE are aware of some important flaws in this version and have dealt with those for COLLECT validation and reporting.  ESS will provide fileset 2702 to deal with these issues but it will not be released until after census.
  5.  Schools therefore have the choice whether to upload the census on Fileset 2701. Once the file is uploaded the revised validation and reports will be applied in COLLECT and more accurate results will be provided to the school for them to take necessary action.
  6.  Schools can wait for Fileset 2702 to be made available and can use the revised validation and summary report to take action before the return is uploaded to COLLECT.  If this choice is taken then schools would expect to receive results from COLLECT validation and reports that are in line with the results the received in SIMS.
  7.  We will make Fileset 2702 available as soon as it is released to all schools.

If you require  further support please reach out to the helpdesk in the usual manner.

Should you need any further support, please contact the School ICT helpdesk by emailing: helpdesk@schoolicts.co.uk<mailto:helpdesk@schoolicts.co.uk> or calling: 0345 222 6802.

Good Afternoon Vanessa,

Thank you for raising this case regarding Registration & Admissions-
Accepted PreAdmissions. Please see the attached patch as requested along
with documentation on applying patches using DBUpgrade below.
How to run a patch through DBupgrade
KB0024145

How to run a patch through DBupgrade
66-B5Q2F0
Notes

How to apply a patch using DBupgrade.exe.
Workaround

1. Extract all of the patch files from the file you were sent *(onto your
Desktop, for example).*

For example, if you were sent or have "Patch 22573.zip", please extract
this to produce three more files. This includes:

3.61.870 to 3.62.999 22573 Patch.XML
3.61.870 to 3.62.999 22573 Patch.ZIP
3.61.870 to 3.62.999 22573 Patch.ZIP.signature

*Please do not extract the contents of the second .zip file within the
initial .zip file that you were sent.*

2. Run dbUpgrade. This is located in either:

Start > All Programs > SIMS Applications > dbUpgrade
*or:*
C:\Program Files\SIMS\SIMS .net\DBupgrade.exe (*on workstation*)
C:\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL.1\MSSQL\Binn\DBupgrade.exe (*on
SIMS SQL server*)

3. Select '*Run the following SIMS database upgrade file*' and specify the
path to the location of where the patch file (.zip) is.

Using the earlier example, you would point this where the 3.61.870 to
3.62.999 22573 Patch.ZIP file is.

4. Enter the SIMS connection and login details:

- For the '*Server Name*' field, please enter the SIMS Server name and the
SQL Instance the database is hosted on, e.g. *MyServer\SIMS20XX*.
- Enter the name of your SIMS .net database into the '*Database Name*'
field.
- And then login with a SIMS username and password or you can use the SQL
SA user account.


If you are unsure of your server or database name details you can find
these via the menu route Tools | System Information within SIMS for SIMS,
or via the FMSConnect.ini located in C:\Program Files\SIMS\FMSSQL (or
C:\Program Files (x86)\SIMS\FMSSQL depending on your setup) for FMS.

Click '*Login*' once these details have been entered.

*Important Note:** If advised to run the patch as the SA user please
specify SA as the SIMS Username and enter your SA password.*

5. The patch should now show in the list, which then if you click install,
this will apply the patch against the specified database.

Depending on what is being applied, this can take some time to complete and
the dbUpgrade window may become unresponsive during this time. It would be
strongly recommended that this window is left open until it has finished.

*Important Note: It would be advised to apply patches or upgrades at a time
when no SIMS users are logged in.*

I hope this helps.

Kind Regards,

*Emmanuel Appiah-Bonna*



Service Desk Analyst



Tel +44 (0) 3330 150 212

[required] Title: Re:[## 151288 ##] P4 - Hope Sentamu Learning Trust - CrowdStrike -  Alert on the host VOY-SD-S5-13
Description:
Hello team,
 
 CrowdStrike has alerted behaviour on the host 'VOY-SD-S5-13'. The file has been quarantined.
 
 Details on the alert are as follows:
 Scanned file: Filename: 1063c3f7-e1fe-11ee-9738-cc96e53c5efe Specific to this detection: A file meets the machine learning-based AV protection's threshold for malicious files Filepath: D:\cs-1063b9fa-e1fe-11ee-9738-806e6f6e6963\1063c3f7-e1fe-11ee-9738-cc96e53c5efe 
 Investigation conducted on the files hash shows that the file is associated with the file 'Downloader.exe', which has been flagged as malicious by multiple security vendors. The genuine downloader.exe file is a software component of Bitdefender Total Security by Bitdefender. Bitdefender Total Security is a suite of security programs that protect computers against malware, viruses, spyware, trojans and computer worms. Downloader.exe downloads and installs updates for Bitdefender Total Security. 
 
 Although the process has been quarantined, could you please review and verify if this tool used within your environment.
 
 Kind Regards, Feyi Ajibola

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: ESS Service Desk <support@educationsoftwaresolutions.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 7 May 2024 at 15:42
Subject: CS0688328 - Registration & Admissions- Accepted PreAdmissions -
Your Reference: PreAdmission Students
To: <vkeel@ahs.pmat.academy>


Good Afternoon Vanessa,

Thank you for raising this case regarding Registration & Admissions-
Accepted PreAdmissions. Please see the attached patch as requested along
with documentation on applying patches using DBUpgrade below.
How to run a patch through DBupgrade
KB0024145

How to run a patch through DBupgrade
66-B5Q2F0
Notes

How to apply a patch using DBupgrade.exe.
Workaround

1. Extract all of the patch files from the file you were sent *(onto your
Desktop, for example).*

For example, if you were sent or have "Patch 22573.zip", please extract
this to produce three more files. This includes:

3.61.870 to 3.62.999 22573 Patch.XML
3.61.870 to 3.62.999 22573 Patch.ZIP
3.61.870 to 3.62.999 22573 Patch.ZIP.signature

*Please do not extract the contents of the second .zip file within the
initial .zip file that you were sent.*

2. Run dbUpgrade. This is located in either:

Start > All Programs > SIMS Applications > dbUpgrade
*or:*
C:\Program Files\SIMS\SIMS .net\DBupgrade.exe (*on workstation*)
C:\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL.1\MSSQL\Binn\DBupgrade.exe (*on
SIMS SQL server*)

3. Select '*Run the following SIMS database upgrade file*' and specify the
path to the location of where the patch file (.zip) is.

Using the earlier example, you would point this where the 3.61.870 to
3.62.999 22573 Patch.ZIP file is.

4. Enter the SIMS connection and login details:

- For the '*Server Name*' field, please enter the SIMS Server name and the
SQL Instance the database is hosted on, e.g. *MyServer\SIMS20XX*.
- Enter the name of your SIMS .net database into the '*Database Name*'
field.
- And then login with a SIMS username and password or you can use the SQL
SA user account.


If you are unsure of your server or database name details you can find
these via the menu route Tools | System Information within SIMS for SIMS,
or via the FMSConnect.ini located in C:\Program Files\SIMS\FMSSQL (or
C:\Program Files (x86)\SIMS\FMSSQL depending on your setup) for FMS.

Click '*Login*' once these details have been entered.

*Important Note:** If advised to run the patch as the SA user please
specify SA as the SIMS Username and enter your SA password.*

5. The patch should now show in the list, which then if you click install,
this will apply the patch against the specified database.

Depending on what is being applied, this can take some time to complete and
the dbUpgrade window may become unresponsive during this time. It would be
strongly recommended that this window is left open until it has finished.

*Important Note: It would be advised to apply patches or upgrades at a time
when no SIMS users are logged in.*

I hope this helps.

Kind Regards,

[required] Title: Unable to access anything on laptop
Description:
Dear Vital

Today i have been supporting our GRA school and unfortunately i am unable
to access anything at all using my laptop.
Upon arrival at GRA this morning i tried to log in, alas i had to restart
the laptop 3 times before i could see anything.
Since then i can see the google search engine page BUT i cannot access the
Google Drives, cannot access emails, cannot log into any mathematical
online software and web pages.

This has been most problematic today as i was supporting a yr10 class pd1,
teaching a yr8 class pd2 and supporting 2 yr11 lessons pd3. I have had to
ask colleagues to print out materials for these and other yr11 classes i
will be supporting this afternoon.

I also am currently in the process of reviewing and rewriting a new maths
curriculum for next year and instead of doing that today i have had to
forward this email as yet again i cannot access material i need to do this
crucial job.

My 1 main fear now is that the laptop will not function correctly over the
bank holiday weekend and again some valuable curriculum design time could
well be lost again.

I send this email from a PC within the maths dept. at GRA which means it is
not my profile at fault as i can access all i need from this machine but
the laptop is not operational.

Any urgent advice would be most welcome.

Kind regards
Jim

____________________________________________________________________________
Dear all,

I am delighted to let you know Herts Music Service are running two UniSONG days this term on the 20th and 21st of June. UniSONG is a day of singing with Rufus Frowde, a fantastic choral Animateur. The day is an opportunity for children to develop their vocal technique, to sing in parts, and sing with a live band.
This will also give your children the opportunity to perform in an ensemble, musically and creatively, and to expand their musical horizons.

It’s also an opportunity for staff to gain repertoire knowledge and learn about the importance of vocal health. The day will give them some great ideas for teaching singing within your own setting too. Rufus is an excellent vocal leader who has worked with the BBC Singers and the National Youth Choir of Great Britain. He was the Artistic and Musical Director of the 2014, 2016, & 2018 Hertfordshire Galas at the Royal Albert Hall and we are delighted to have him back with us for UniSONG 2024.

We are offering schools the opportunity to bring one year group from upper KS2/Y5 or Y6, but spaces are limited. Places will be allocated on a first come first served basis.

The event is held at St John’s Church, Boxmoor, from 9.30am (arrival anytime from 9.00am so we are ready to start singing at 9.30am) until 3.00pm, with a concert at 2.45pm for parents. Children will need to bring a packed lunch, snack and drink.

Unfortunately, we do not have funding for the day, so there will be a charge of £150 per class for the day.
To sign up, please reply to this email with your school and number of classes you would like to bring.

Please do let me know if you have any questions.
I look forward to hearing from you.
Best wishes,
Tansy Agnew

Herts Music Service is open 7 days a week 8.00am-9.00pm so you may receive e-mails from me in the evenings and at weekends.  Please only respond at a time convenient to you and in your working time.

Dear Vanessa Keel,

Please provide the following article to your IT team, should they need
assistance please ask them to provide direct dials.



This should however be all they need. Take care


How to install SIMS products on a new workstation via SOLUS 3
KB0052384
Introduction

The following article will take you through the process of installing SIMS
on a new workstation using SOLUS 3.

This article assumes that SOLUS 3 has already been installed and configured
on the server.

The steps to install SIMS can also be applied to installing FMS and
Discover.

If a SOLUS 3 agent has already been installed on the workstation, but you
are having issues with the agent and wish to reinstall it, it is highly
recommended to instead follow the steps in the KB article below.

KB0044360 - SOLUS 3 - How to perform a clean uninstallation /
reinstallation of the SOLUS 3 Agent
<https://customer.support-ess.com/csm?id=kb_article_view&sysparm_article=KB0044360>


If installing SIMS on the workstation for the first time, please continue
with the steps below to add the new workstation in to the SOLUS 3
environment.
Instructions

1) On the server, open *SOLUS 3 Deployment Server UI *using the shortcut on
the *Desktop*

2) Navigate to *Environment | Targets | Clients*

3) Click the *Add* button

4) Place a *tick* in to the products that you wish to have installed e.g.
*SIMS*, *SIMS Discover*, *FMS*

5) Click the *Choose Clients* button

6) Locate the new workstation on your *Network*. You can also locate the
workstation by browsing your domain's Active Directory by selecting
the *AD* radio
button. Alternatively, if you know the workstation's hostname or IP
address, this can be entered in to the field at the bottom and SOLUS 3 will
attempt to detect it.

7) Click the arrow to move the workstation over to the *SELECTED
COMPUTERS* section
and click *OK*

8) You will be prompted to enter the *Domain\Administrator* credentials.

9) Click *Save*

10) SOLUS 3 will now attempt to install an Agent on to the new workstation.
The status of this can be viewed within *Environment | Agents | Agents*



11) Once the installation of the Agent has finished, the selected product
will then automatically begin to download and install on to the desired
workstation.

12) Staff who are currently using the workstation will notice the following
popup from the SOLUS 3 Agent  in the Windows system tray.

13) Staff can hasten the deployment of SIMS by clicking the *Deploy Now* button
which will skip the 2 minute timer.



14) The desired product (be it SIMS, FMS or Discover) will then begin to
install on to the workstation.

15) When the deployment has finished, you will see the following message in
the *SOLUS 3 Agent Notifier* window and the user can now launch the
software via the Windows *START* menu and log in.







Kind regards,

*Matt Scotton*

[required] Title: Re: Ongoing IT issues in Music
Description:
Hello All

I'll do my best to clarify the problems that exist with the M1 music
computers. All of the issues have been highlighted for some time (over two
years) right back to when Kevin was out IT tech in school. Unfortunately
the lack of a consistent tech has not helped, but Rachid is aware of them
and seeking solutions.

*PROBLEM 1*

There is a problem with some Macs connecting to the network on the far wall
in particular. Both Holly and now Rachid have highlighted the problem could
be with the old network switches they are connected to.

Solution: test and potentially upgrade the switches for L40 and test the
individual connections.

*PROBLEM 2*

Password reset. The Macs seem to request user password changes much more
often than other computers in school. On top of this there seems to be some
synchronization issues when changing.

Change the password reset settings potentially avoiding requests on the
macs and limit to PCs only?

*PROBLEM 3*

Websites blocked

Could we have a way of predicting when the permissions are to expire and
reset before lessons are disrupted.

*PROBLEM 4*

The hard drives of the macs are now filling restricting software upgrades
and general usage.

The solution to this could be much more complicated. The problem seems to
be caused by the way they have been configured to integrate into the
windows based system used by the rest of the school. The mac I use in the
studio has not got this problem so I suspect it is caused by data (system
data) as a consequence of having multiple users in their present
configuration. I would suggest looking at reconfiguring the macs and
creating a seperate network for the department. There would still need to
be internet for google classroom and drive but could be configured for
optimum mac use.



There have of course been school wide internet issues this week that have
added to the problems but hopefully these are now fixed.

Unfortunately I am not a network specialist and don't have access to the
software etc to solve these problems but happy to discuss and help Rachid
and Vital where I can

Dave

[required] Title: Urgent - Huntington Trust-e SIMS extractor Schedule Task Still Not Working
Description:
Marcus and I have looked at the issue as I had previously escalated a ticket about this problem. I thought it had been solved and that it was just an issue with a SIMS update that wasn't working correctly, but there are still problems after fixing the SIMS update loop.

New pupils are not being added to the cashless system, adjustments to free school meals are not being updated, and some payments made by parents are not added to students' accounts.  I've asked Civica at least four times now if they can take a look to see if they can see any reason why it is not working, and they either don't respond or take a look and say they can't see any issues or there must be a problem with the data from the MIS. The data is all correct on the MIS.

It's been ongoing for quite some time now, there is a scheduled task on the HS-Cashless01 server that is meant to run the Trust-e SIMS extractor sync automatically every weekday at 07:30, I don't know if there is a problem with this scheduled task and that this is where the problem lies.

Please can someone look into this issue as the school is getting increasingly frustrated that this has not been sorted and I'm at a loss for what else to do.

Nothing loading
Chris

I need some help investigating an issue with the tills in the dining hall at Huntington School.

The kitchen manager has told me that at least one of the tills (not always the same one) and sometimes multiple tills will lose connection to the server every day.

Most of the tills in the dining hall are connected wirelessly, there is one with a wired connection. I have made sure that the APs are up to date, a technician from Civica did a remote session recently and looked at the event viewer logs and concluded that there was an issue with the network in some way, but didn't give any more detail about what the issue was.

It's a sporadic but consistent issue, that never seems to affect all of the tills at the same time, a few will lose connection to the server, while the rest of the tills will remain connected.

Any help would be greatly appreciated in getting to the bottom of this, as when a till goes offline during service it can take up to 5 minutes to reconnect, and at peak times that slows service down dramatically.

Cheers,
James
